  "body": "I am new to `reactjs` and trying to install `babel` to run `babel code` without serving HTTP file. By following the [Package Manager](https://facebook.github.io/react/docs/package-management.html) I have installed it with `browserify` as:\n\n```\n$ npm install --save react react-dom babelify babel-preset-react\n$ browserify -t [ babelify ] main.js -o bundle.js\n```\n\nAfter it I created the file `.babelrc` in the same root directory with following code \n\n```\n{ \"presets\": [\"react\"] }\n```\n\nAnd removed the HTTP `babel-core` source file as:\n\n```\n<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n  <head>\n    <meta charset=\"utf-8\" />\n    <title>React Tutorial</title>\n    <script src=\"build/react.js\"></script>\n    <script src=\"build/react-dom.js\"></script>\n    <!-- removed https://npmcdn.com/babel-core@5.8.38/browser.min.js -->\n  </head>\n  <body>\n    <div id=\"content\"></div>\n    <script type=\"text/babel\">\n      ReactDOM.render(\n        <h1>Hello, world!</h1>,\n        document.getElementById('content')\n      );\n    </script>\n  </body>\n</html>\n```\n\nbut when I access it from `http://localhost/react/` this does't work. I have very trouble Please Help me to solve it.\n\nThank You in advance...\n",
